    },
    {
      "id": "el_20",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1005,
      "y": 419,
      "width": 406,
      "height": 250,
      "text": "Cycle period 4: digits 2,3,7,8\n  2: 2,4,8,6  |  3: 3,9,7,1\n  7: 7,9,3,1  |  8: 8,4,2,6\nCycle period 2: digits 4,9\n  4: 4,6      |  9: 9,1\nCycle period 1: 0,1,5,6 (always same)\n\nFind n mod period → pick from cycle\nIf mod=0, use LAST value in cycle\n\nWHY: Unit digit of a^n depends only on unit digit of\na\n  Multiplying repeats a fixed cycle in mod 10\n\nEx: Unit digit of 3^7 → period=4, 7 mod 4=3\n  3rd in cycle(3,9,7,1) → 7. So unit digit=7 ✓",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 2000,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 20,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f5"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Cycle period 4: digits 2,3,7,8\n  2: 2,4,8,6  |  3: 3,9,7,1\n  7: 7,9,3,1  |  8: 8,4,2,6\nCycle period 2: digits 4,9\n  4: 4,6      |  9: 9,1\nCycle period 1: 0,1,5,6 (always same)\n\nFind n mod period → pick from cycle\nIf mod=0, use LAST value in cycle\n\nWHY: Unit digit of a^n depends only on unit digit of\na\n  Multiplying repeats a fixed cycle in mod 10\n\nEx: Unit digit of 3^7 → period=4, 7 mod 4=3\n  3rd in cycle(3,9,7,1) → 7. So unit digit=7 ✓",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
