    {
      "id": "el_71",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 65,
      "y": 1996,
      "width": 303,
      "height": 188,
      "text": "LOGIC:\nStep 1: (x+2)/(y+3)=3/4→4x-3y=1...(1)\n  (x-3)/(y-2)=1/3→3x-y=7...(2)\nStep 2: From(2):y=3x-7. In(1):4x-3(3x-7)=1\n  4x-9x+21=1→x=4, y=5\n  Check: 6/8=3/4✓ 1/3=1/3✓\n\nTRICK (substitution):\nGet y from simpler eq, plug into other\nFrom 3x-y=7→y=3x-7 (quick!)\nThen solve single variable\n\nAnswer: Fraction = 4/5 ✓",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 12,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
